<GuideLayout title={title} description={description} cluster="after-builders">

<p>Plaster dust spreads easily through a property after renovation work. Fine gypsum particles settle on floors, walls, surfaces and inside ventilation systems.</p>

<h2>Why plaster dust spreads through a property</h2>
<p>Cutting plasterboard and sanding filler releases extremely fine dust. Without correct removal methods it redistributes rather than being removed.</p>

<h2>Correct removal process</h2>
<p>Professional after builders cleaning uses HEPA filtration vacuum systems followed by damp microfibre wiping to capture remaining particles.</p>

</GuideLayout>

